// =============================================================================
// DAX — v6 — Hourly Battery Profile Chart Measures
// File    : 64_dax_v6_hourly_chart.dax
// Date    : 2026-05-10
//
// PURPOSE:
//   Powers the "24h Battery Behavior by Strategy" visual (V6) on Page 9.
//   Data source: gold_battery_hourly_profile (96 rows: 4 strategies × 24 hours)
//
// VISUAL TYPE: Line and Clustered Column Chart (Combo)
//   - Column (bars): [V6 Charge Rate] + [V6 Discharge Rate]
//     → Blue bars = charging, Amber bars = discharging
//   - Line (primary right axis): [V6 SoC Pct]
//     → Green line, 0–100 axis
//   - Line (secondary or primary right): [V6 Grid Price EUR MWh]
//     → Grey dashed line, 0–150 axis
//
// SLICER:
//   Add a DEDICATED slicer for this chart only:
//   → gold_battery_hourly_profile[strategy_label]  (single select)
//   → Do NOT sync with S2 (different table, different grain)
//   → Position: above or beside the V6 chart
//
// HOW IT WORKS:
//   When user selects "Peak-Shaving" in the dedicated slicer:
//     - gold_battery_hourly_profile is filtered to strategy = "peak_shaving"
//     - 24 rows remain (one per hour)
//     - All 4 measures below evaluate in that filtered context
//     - Bars show charging 00h–06h, discharging 07h–20h
//     - Price line shows WHY (cheapest at night → charge, expensive morning → discharge)
//
// NOTE: No Legend field needed in the visual — each measure is its own named series.
//   The measure names appear in the legend automatically.
// =============================================================================


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 1. V6 Charge Rate
//
// Y-axis: Column (bars), left axis, 0–1.0 scale (0% to 100% of max power)
// Color: Blue (#00B4D8)
// Label in legend: "Charge ↑"
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[V6 Charge Rate] =
AVERAGE(gold_battery_hourly_profile[charge_rate])


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 2. V6 Discharge Rate
//
// Y-axis: Column (bars), left axis, 0–1.0 scale
// Color: Amber (#F4A261)
// Label in legend: "Discharge ↓"
//
// NOTE: discharge values are positive (0–1). The visual represents
//   this as "energy leaving the battery" — bars will show alongside
//   charge bars but they are mutually exclusive per hour by design.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[V6 Discharge Rate] =
AVERAGE(gold_battery_hourly_profile[discharge_rate])


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 3. V6 SoC Pct
//
// Y-axis: Line, right axis, scale 0–100 (%)
// Color: Green (#2DC653)
// Label in legend: "SoC %"
//
// Shows the battery's state of charge at each hour of the day.
// Peak-Shaving: 72% at midnight → 99% at 04h → falls to 8% by 14h → 58% by 23h
// Backup: flat 83–90% throughout (always ready)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[V6 SoC Pct] =
AVERAGE(gold_battery_hourly_profile[soc_percent])


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 4. V6 Price Index
//
// Y-axis: Line, right axis, scale 0–150
// Color: Light grey (#AAAAAA), dashed
// Label in legend: "Fiyat Endeksi (100=Ort.)"  or  "Price Index (100=avg)"
//
// WHY PRICE INDEX instead of €/MWh or €/kWh:
//   - €/MWh values (34–115) work on the right axis but unit is unintuitive for end users
//   - €/kWh values (0.034–0.115) are too small and become invisible on a 0–100 axis
//   - Price Index (100 = daily average) sits naturally on the 0–150 axis alongside SoC
//     → Values below 100: cheap hours → batteries should charge
//     → Values above 100: expensive hours → batteries should discharge
//     → Immediately readable without knowing electricity market units
//
// SCALE:
//   gold_battery_hourly_profile[grid_price_index] is pre-computed in notebook 13:
//     price_index = round((price_eur_mwh / daily_avg_price) × 100, 1)
//     daily_avg_price ≈ 78.3 €/MWh (DE representative 2023–2025)
//   Range: 00h (34 €/MWh) → index 43.4  |  19h (115 €/MWh) → index 146.9
//   Right axis: Min 0, Max 150 → fits both SoC (0–100) and price index (44–147)
//
// NOTE: Price signal is the same for all strategies — the index shows WHY
//   each strategy chooses to charge/discharge at specific hours.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[V6 Price Index] =
AVERAGE(gold_battery_hourly_profile[grid_price_index])


// =============================================================================
// POWER BI SETUP — STEP BY STEP
//
// STEP 1 — ADD DEDICATED SLICER (above or beside V6 chart)
//   Insert → Slicer
//   Field: gold_battery_hourly_profile[strategy_label]
//   Slicer style: Dropdown or Tile (single select)
//   Default selection: "Peak-Shaving"
//   ⚠ Do NOT sync with S2 (S2 = gold_battery_dispatch, different table)
//   ⚠ Do NOT sync with S1 (building slicer — irrelevant for this reference table)
//
// STEP 2 — INSERT VISUAL
//   Insert → Line and Clustered Column Chart
//   (Power BI: combo chart icon in Visualizations panel)
//
// STEP 3 — FIELD BINDINGS
//   X-axis (shared)   : gold_battery_hourly_profile[hour_label]
//   Column Y-axis      : [V6 Charge Rate]       (label: Charge ↑)
//   Column Y-axis      : [V6 Discharge Rate]    (label: Discharge ↓)
//   Line Y-axis        : [V6 SoC Pct]           (label: SoC %)
//   Line Y-axis        : [V6 Grid Price EUR MWh] (label: Price €/MWh)
//   Legend             : leave EMPTY (do not add strategy_label here)
//
// STEP 4 — FIX X-AXIS SORT
//   Go to Data view → gold_battery_hourly_profile table
//   Select hour_label column → Column tools → Sort by Column → hour_of_day
//   This fixes the X-axis from showing 00:00 at random position.
//
// STEP 5 — FORMAT THE VISUAL
//
//   Columns:
//     [V6 Charge Rate]      → Color: #00B4D8 (teal/blue)
//     [V6 Discharge Rate]   → Color: #F4A261 (amber/orange)
//
//   Lines:
//     [V6 SoC Pct]          → Color: #2DC653 (green), Width: 2.5px
//     [V6 Grid Price EUR MWh] → Color: #AAAAAA (grey), Width: 1.5px, Style: Dashed
//
//   Y-axis (Column — left):
//     Min: 0, Max: 1.0
//     Title: "Charge / Discharge Rate"
//     Display units: None
//
//   Y-axis (Line — right):
//     Min: 0, Max: 115 (slightly above max price)
//     Title: "SoC (%) / Price (€/MWh)"
//     Show secondary: ON
//
//   X-axis:
//     Font size: 8pt
//     All 24 labels must show — set Min category width to small value
//
//   Title: "24h Battery Behavior by Strategy"
//   Subtitle: bind [V6 Strategy Logic Label] (from file 63_dax_v52_eu_compliance_fix.dax)
//     → Shows one-line logic: "Charges 00h–07h (night, off-peak) · Discharges 07h–20h"
//
//   Legend: ON (auto — shows measure names as series)
//   Legend position: Bottom
//
// STEP 6 — ADD REFERENCE LINES (optional but recommended)
//   Analytics pane → Y-axis constant line:
//   - SoC Min: 10 (grey dashed — minimum safe SoC)
//   - SoC Target: 80 (green dashed — optimal charge target)
//
// =============================================================================
//
// WHAT THE CHART SHOWS (reading guide for energy manager):
//
//   Peak-Shaving selected:
//     Blue bars 00h–06h → battery charging at night when price is 34–48 €/MWh
//     Amber bars 07h–20h → battery discharging during peak hours 85–115 €/MWh
//     Green line drops from 99% (04h) to 8% (14h) — near empty at afternoon peak
//     Grey line shows the price curve — bars clearly follow the price signal
//
//   Self-Consumption selected:
//     Blue bars 10h–15h → charging from PV generation (midday solar peak)
//     Amber bars 18h–23h → discharging in evening when PV stops
//     Green line: charges up to 92% by 14h, empties to 8% by 23h
//     Grey price line: PV generation at midday DESPITE slightly higher prices
//
//   Time-of-Use selected:
//     Blue bars 00h–06h → maximum charge rate (cheapest EPEX hours)
//     Amber bars 08h–20h → full discharge during expensive hours
//     Green line: 99% by 06h → 5% by 16h → recovering by 23h
//     Most aggressive arbitrage strategy — highest charge/discharge rates
//
//   Backup selected:
//     Very small blue bars (maintenance charge only, 0.30 rate)
//     Tiny amber bars 09h–14h (opportunistic only, 0.12–0.18 rate)
//     Green line: flat 82–90% all day — always ready for emergency
//     Grey price line: strategy IGNORES price signal — safety priority
//
// =============================================================================
